<!-- Node: "Softimage | XSI EXP for Half-Life 2 released" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Softimage | XSI EXP for Half-Life 2 released</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/4" title="View user profile.">Olpainless</a> on Thursday, March 25, 2004 - 15:56</small><br /><br />
As pointed out on the <a href="http://forums.gamedesign.net" target="_blank">Rust forums</a> by Wolv, the animation tools for Half-Life 2 models has been released. (More details available in <a href="http://forums.gamedesign.net/viewtopic.php?t=6116" target="_blank">this thread.</a><br />
<br />
From the website:<br />
<i>"Whether you are a 3-D professional, a novice or just curious, the XSI EXP for Half-Life 2 guides you through all the features and functionality in SOFTIMAGE|XSI, and lets you actually output Half-Life 2 characters and models. From polygon modeling and lightning fast Subdivision Surfaces, to nonlinear animation mixing and interactive simulation and rendering, it is all here. "</i>
<br /><br />
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/209#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">1 comment</a> &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/209" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


