<div class="body_box_header">New Hosted Site at RUST</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/8" title="View user profile.">Jherax</a> on Sunday, March 21, 2004 - 01:32</small><br /><br />
RUST would like to give a warm welcome to Kingpin_Xatrix who is now officially hosted at <a href="http://kingpin_xatrix.gamedesign.net/">http://kingpin_xatrix.gamedesign.net/</a>. Kingpin_Xatrix's site has quite a few Kingpin related tutorials and a few other interesting tidbits, including an <a href="http://kingpin_xatrix.gamedesign.net/interview.htm">interview with Rafael Paiz</a>, one of the KP programmers.<br />
<br />
If you run an editing-related website and are looking for a new host, feel free to contact either Gard or myself with some information about your site.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/208#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">2 comments</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Interview with Realdespair" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Interview with Realdespair</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/90" title="View user profile.">realdespair</a> on Sunday, March 14, 2004 - 01:11</small><br /><br />
<p>Taking time from his very busy schedule, up and comming mapper RD (RealDespair), answered some questions from RUST, on the art of mapping and being a good mapper.</p>

<p align="center"><Img  border="0" width="250" src = "http://www.pitrd.com/pit/website/maps/screenshots/rambohulk/hulk2.JPG"></br>Fy_Rambohulk</p>

<p><b>RUST:</b> You are probably one of the most well known Mapper's here on RUST and on the Gamedesign.Net forums. Your work has been widely excepted by the Mapping Community as great mapping, recieving some great reviews. How did you come into mapping, what inspired you download an map editor?
<br /><br />
